  "name": "Pancreatic Cancer - Elevated CA 19-9 Query",
  "description": "Tests ability to find pancreatic cancer patients via elevated CA 19-9 tumor marker (>100 U/mL is highly suggestive; normal <37 U/mL). Includes Path D (elevated CA 19-9 without formal pancreatic cancer dx).",
  "prompt": "Find patients with elevated CA 19-9 tumor marker results greater than 100 U/mL.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients with high CA 19-9.",
    "broad": "Find patients with CA 19-9 (cancer antigen 19-9) measurements above 100 U/mL — highly suggestive of pancreatic cancer (also elevated in cholangiocarcinoma and pancreatitis).",
    "expert": "I need to identify patients with markedly elevated CA 19-9, a tumor marker that is highly suggestive of pancreatic malignancy when substantially elevated. Search Observation resources for CA 19-9 results using the appropriate LOINC code for Cancer Antigen 19-9 in serum or plasma, and filter to values above one hundred units per milliliter — well above the normal cutoff and in the range associated with malignancy. This path captures patients with significant tumor-marker elevation who may not yet carry a formal pancreatic cancer diagnosis."
  },
